# -- $4: LESSONS LEARNED --
LNG:skill_first{CODEC-CORTEX public narrative must open with Universal Skill and contextual memory protocol, not codec-first compression}
LNG:status_honesty{Every capability must be current/specification/planned/future when maturity matters}
LNG:reversibility_scope{Structural reversibility belongs to codec roundtrip targets; HCORTEX provides contextual reversibility for humans; literal full-history reconstruction is not promised}
LNG:benchmark_integrity{Numeric density or performance claims require reproducible benchmarks before public measured language}
LNG:result_location{External audit artifacts requested after release belong in ../docs, not inside the published codec-cortex repository}
LNG:git_scope{Stage only scoped files; preserve parent workspace changes and artifacts outside the repo unless explicitly requested}

